A federal appeals court on Thursday blocked a court order demanding changes to the arrest and search program at the New York Police Department and dismissed the judge from the case.
A second U.S. federal appeals court said Judge Shira Scheindlin's decision would be postponed until the city filed an appeal.
The judge ruled in August that the city had violated the Constitution by implementing its program of stopping and questioning people.
