When asked about their views on specific policy areas - from monopoly regulations to product laws - most entrepreneurs expressed the view that scrutiny of these key competences should return to Westminster.
There was widespread dissatisfaction with the single market, and entrepreneurs said that the costs of Brussels regulations now outweighed the benefits of being part of the European business sphere, with even 40 percent of large companies, traditionally the most pro-European companies, agreeing.
Finally, our survey of business leaders revealed the most telling knowledge, namely that an overwhelming majority wants Britain to seek a treaty change and a relationship with the EU that should be based on trade, not politics.
The findings, shared by businesses of all sizes and major business groups, show that the business sector is pushing for “meaningful change” that will bring influence back to the UK.
